gameRecap.title: Game Recap: 76ers 135, Raptors 120
gameRecap.excerpt: The Sixers snap a three-game streak as they defeat the Raptors, 130-118. Kelly Oubre led the Sixers with a season-high 32 points, along with seven rebounds and three assists as Cameron Payne added 24 points. Gary Trent Jr. led the Raptors with 23 points. The 76ers move to 40-35 as the Raptors fall to 23-51.
